    <Heading>
      Spacetrace Overview
    </Heading>

    <BodyText>
      Spacetrace is a tool used to analyze footprint of mozilla
      invented by <html:a href="mailto:blythe@netscape.com">Garrett Blythe <Email>blythe@netscape.com</Email></html:a>
    </BodyText>

    <SubHeading>What spacetrace can do :</SubHeading>
    <List>
      <ListItem>It is a Post analysis (non-realtime) tool - you run with test case, get data file
      and analyze it.</ListItem>
      <ListItem>Amount of live memory held by app at any
      instant</ListItem>
      <ListItem>Allocator overhead is factored into the
      calculation</ListItem>
      <ListItem>Query and browsing of allocations done by
      app</ListItem>
      <ListItem>Report Leaks</ListItem>
    </List>

